Name of kernel : uname -a ou uname -r

/boot/vmlinuz-$(uname -r) : bootable kernel image
/boot/config-$(uname -r) : record of config param 
/boot/initrd-$(uname -r) : initial RAM disk, early root filesystem, allow to get device drivers
System.map-$(uname -r) : symbol table
grub/grub.cfg : GRUB bootloader configuration file, contains entries for installed kernel

Kernel module : object file, can be load into the kernel, provides new functionnality to the kernel
modules located in /lib/modules/$(uname -r)/kernel as .ko files

lsmod : modules currently loaded
modprobe <module> : load module
modinfo <module> : info on the module

/proc/kallsyms : 


